Method Detail

getStream

java.io.InputStream getStream()
Returns an InputStream by which the content of the model can be read to be parsed by an RDF parser or other RDF parsing tools.

Returns:
InputStream for the RDF. Should be closed at the end, but also cannot be used more than once. To read the RDF again, this method must be called again.

getEtag

java.util.Date getEtag()
The etag of a model is a representation of the version of the entire model while each individual resource in that model may have their own etag to reflect on their individual versions. It is possible that no such value is maintained in the model.

Returns:
a Date representing the etag of the entire model, or null if such is not possible to maintain in the model.
